---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SiteNav from "../components/SiteNav.astro";
import SiteFooter from "../components/SiteFooter.astro";
import Hero from "../components/Hero.astro";
import SectionHead from "../components/SectionHead.astro";
import ProblemTile from "../components/ProblemTile.astro";
import EngageCard from "../components/EngageCard.astro";
import EngagePanel from "../components/EngagePanel.astro";
import AboutBlock from "../components/AboutBlock.astro";
import ContactSection from "../components/ContactSection.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Lantern Strategic — Helping businesses move forward when the path isn't obvious."
  description="Operations & technology consulting for owners and operators navigating the unnoticed friction slowing their business down."
>
  <SiteNav />
  <Hero />

  <section id="approach" class="problems">
    <div class="container">
      <SectionHead eyebrow="The approach" heading="The problems that don't announce themselves.">
        <p>
          Most of the friction in a business doesn't announce itself. It's the third meeting
          about the same thing. The workaround that became the process. The report that takes
          a full day to pull together, originally built to answer a question nobody asks anymore.
        </p>
      </SectionHead>

      <p class="pull-line">
        These <em class="crimson">quiet problems</em> are the ones easiest to live with —
        and hardest to fix from the inside.
      </p>
      <p class="problems-body">
        The friction becomes the background. The workaround becomes the process. And the cost
        compounds in ways nobody's tracking. Lantern Strategic is built to address the quiet
        problems — the ones that don't show up in a dashboard, but show up in everyone's calendar.
      </p>

      <div class="problem-grid">
        <ProblemTile num="01" heading="The third meeting about the same thing.">
          Decisions that keep coming back because no one named who actually owns them.
        </ProblemTile>
        <ProblemTile num="02" heading="A process everyone has a workaround for.">
          The map and the territory drifted apart years ago. Nobody flagged it.
        </ProblemTile>
        <ProblemTile num="03" heading="The day-long report no one reads.">
          Built for a question that mattered once. Still costs a day every month.
        </ProblemTile>
        <ProblemTile num="04" heading="Recurring meetings that outlived their purpose.">
          The calendar fills up faster than anyone removes from it. Attention pays the bill.
        </ProblemTile>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="engage" class="engagements">
    <div class="container">
      <SectionHead eyebrow="Engagements" heading="Three ways to engage.">
        <p>
          Every business is at a different point in the conversation. Engagements are scoped
          to fit; pricing is project-based or retainer.
        </p>
      </SectionHead>

      <div class="engage-grid">
        <EngageCard
          num="01"
          category="Defined projects"
          heading="A clear scope, a specific outcome."
          examples="Technology evaluations · AI training · focused operational assessments."
        >
          Flat fee. Defined deliverable. For when you already know what you need handled
          and want it handled cleanly.
          <Fragment slot="when-it-fits"><b>When it fits —</b> the problem is named, the scope is known.</Fragment>
        </EngageCard>
        <EngageCard
          num="02"
          category="Discovery & plan"
          heading="Sit with the business. Learn how it actually runs."
          examples="A defined period of listening, observing, and structuring."
        >
          We produce a plan you can execute — or hand back to us to run. For when you know
          something needs to change but naming it cleanly is part of the work.
          <Fragment slot="when-it-fits"><b>When it fits —</b> the symptom is loud, the diagnosis is not yet.</Fragment>
        </EngageCard>
        <EngageCard
          num="03"
          category="Embedded expertise"
          heading="Senior operations thinking, on your team."
          examples="Fractional executive support · coaching · on-site training · office hours."
        >
          A sounding board for the calls that don't fit anywhere else. For when the value
          is in having someone to think with, not just a deliverable to receive.
          <Fragment slot="when-it-fits"><b>When it fits —</b> the work is ongoing, the questions keep coming.</Fragment>
        </EngageCard>
      </div>

      <EngagePanel />
    </div>
  </section>

  <AboutBlock />

  <ContactSection />

  <SiteFooter />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .problems {
    background: var(--color-parchment-2);
    padding: clamp(72px, 9vw, 130px) 0;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }
  .container {
    max-width: var(--max-content);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--gutter);
  }
  .pull-line {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(22px, 2.4vw, 32px);
    line-height: 1.32;
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    max-width: 28ch;
    text-wrap: balance;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .pull-line .crimson {
    color: var(--color-crimson);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .problems-body {
    margin-top: 28px;
    max-width: 60ch;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-charcoal) 88%, transparent);
  }
  .problem-grid {
    margin-top: clamp(40px, 5vw, 64px);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--color-stone);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-stone);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-stone);
  }
  @media (min-width: 760px) {
    .problem-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }
  @media (min-width: 1080px) {
    .problem-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    }
  }
  .engagements {
    background: var(--color-parchment);
    padding: clamp(72px, 9vw, 130px) 0;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }
  .engage-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 20px;
  }
  @media (min-width: 880px) {
    .engage-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 24px;
    }
  }
</style>
